<subSubSection id="22E34B2B32A1A9AE0009B61FF23665AA" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" type="taxon discussion">
<paragraph id="63DF41A2975BF24810221D731DC347E2" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">Taxon discussion</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CCF274335B74167FF798026DE555C8DA" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">
In Greece, this subspecies is reported only from the floristic region of NC Greece, where it occurs on Mt. Voras (also known as Kaimaktsalan) and Mt. Varnous (
<bibRefCitation id="23A58534442BC8594515EFB9CA735184" author="Anagnostopoulos, A." journalOrPublisher="ARG Gantner Verlag KG, Ruggell" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" refId="B7667693" refString="Anagnostopoulos, A., Strid, A., 2002. Flora Hellenica 2. ARG Gantner Verlag KG, Ruggell" title="Flora Hellenica 2" year="2002">Anagnostopoulos and Strid 2002</bibRefCitation>
). This is the third report from Greece (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="7F9FA265395D4E4A3649C35306127E06" captionStart="Figure 22" captionStartId="F7677696" captionText="Figure 22. Saxifraga pedemontana subsp. cymosa from Mt. Rodopi (photo: P. Doumas)." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e81817.figure22" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/640579" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">22</figureCitation>
) and the first one from the floristic region of the NE (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="1EB582876266F04481BC23317B765008" captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="F7677669" captionText="Figure 17. Distribution map of Convolvulus suendermannii, Lomelosia rhodopensis, Drymocallis rupestris and Saxifraga pedemontana subsp. cymosa in Greece." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e81817.figure17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/656581" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">17</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
